HEADWORD: Manciple
<hw>Man"ci*ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From OF.
<ets>mancipe</ets> slave, servant (with <ets>l</ets> inserted, as in
<ets>participle</ets>), fr. L. <ets>mancipium</ets>. See
<er>Mancipate</er>.]</ety> <def>A steward; a purveyor, particularly of a
college or Inn of Court.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mancona bark</ent>⟦br⟧
